		<a name="top" id="top"></a>
				<h1 class="firstHeading">XML Elements</h1>
		<div id="bodyContent">
			<h3 id="siteSub">From ScWiki</h3>
			<div id="contentSub"></div>
									<div id="jump-to-nav">Jump to: <a href="#column-one">navigation</a>, <a href="#searchInput">search</a></div>			<!-- start content -->
			<p>Elements are the sub-atomic particles of the chemistry of  Wasabi UI development.  They represent the binding of fonts, colors, and raster graphics to id's which are then referenced by the actual objects of the system.  The definition of elements should occur hierarchically within an &lt;elements&gt; tag.  Because elements are intended to be referenced by GuiObjects, specifying elements without ids is a meaningless endeavour.  A simple sample of each possible type of element would look like this:
</p>
<pre>&lt;elements&gt;
	&lt;color id="myindigo" value="64,32,128"/&gt; 
	&lt;bitmap id="mybitmap" file="mybitmap.png" x="104" y="0" h="90" w="244" gammagroup="Backgrounds"/&gt;
	&lt;bitmapfont id="mybitfont" file="myfont.png" charwidth="9" charheight="13" hspacing="3" vspacing="1"/&gt;
	&lt;truetypefont id="myttfont" file="impact.ttf"/&gt;
	&lt;elementalias id="newelemid" target="mybitmap"/&gt;
&lt;/elements&gt;
</pre>
<p><br />
</p>
<table id="toc" class="toc" summary="Contents"><tr><td><div id="toctitle"><h2>Contents</h2></div>
<ul>
<li class="toclevel-1"><a href="#.3Cbitmap.2F.3E"><span class="tocnumber">1</span> <span class="toctext">&lt;bitmap/&gt;</span></a></li>
<li class="toclevel-1"><a href="#.3Cbitmapfont.2F.3E"><span class="tocnumber">2</span> <span class="toctext">&lt;bitmapfont/&gt;</span></a></li>
<li class="toclevel-1"><a href="#.3Ctruetypefont.2F.3E"><span class="tocnumber">3</span> <span class="toctext">&lt;truetypefont/&gt;</span></a></li>
<li class="toclevel-1"><a href="#.3Ccolor.2F.3E"><span class="tocnumber">4</span> <span class="toctext">&lt;color/&gt;</span></a></li>
